 wide range of symptoms after experiencing a traumatic event. Flashbacks, nightmares, intrusive thoughts, anxiety, avoidance, mood, and thinking changes are all possible.<\\/p><p><em>Social anxiety disorder (SAD)<\\/em> is a mental health condition characterized by a fear of being judged badly in social situations, such as performing or speaking in front of everyone.<\\/p><p><strong>Causes of Anxiety<\\/strong><br \\/>Researchers are discovering more about these links all the time.<\\/p><ul><li>Imagining the future<\\/li><li>Genetics<\\/li><li>Environment<\\/li><li>Intense stress level<\\/li><li>Brain changes<\\/li><li>Trauma<\\/li><\\/ul><p><strong>Treatment of Anxiety<\\/strong><br \\/>Anxiety problems are typically treated successfully with psychotherapy and lifestyle changes, either alone or in combination with medication. One of the most successful treatments is cognitive-behavioral therapy (CBT), which is targeted at an individual\'s specific worries. Patients are taught to question the faulty mental patterns that cause them so much pain.<\\/p>\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Roboto Slab\",\"typography_font_weight\":\"400\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
