 wide range of symptoms after experiencing a traumatic event. Flashbacks, nightmares, intrusive thoughts, anxiety, avoidance, mood, and thinking changes are all possible.<\\/p><p><em>Social anxiety disorder (SAD)<\\/em> is a mental health condition characterized by a fear of being judged badly in social situations, such as performing or speaking in front of everyone.<\\/p><p><strong>Causes of Anxiety<\\/strong><br \\/>Researchers are discovering more about these links all the time.<br \\/>Imagining the future<br \\/>Genetics<br \\/>Environment<br \\/>Intense stress level<br \\/>Brain changes<br \\/>Trauma<\\/p><p><strong>Treatment of Anxiety<\\/strong><br \\/>Anxiety problems are typically treated successfully with psychotherapy and lifestyle changes, either alone or in combination with medication. One of the most successful treatments is cognitive-behavioral therapy (CBT), which is targeted at an individual\'s specific worries. Patients are taught to question the faulty mental patterns that cause them so much pain.<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
