(1438, 169, '_elementor_data', '[{\"id\":\"1a1388b\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"4573775a\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"7c40bbc\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"image\":{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/localhost\\/aira\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/07\\/pexels-dids-5616284.jpg\",\"id\":263}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"image\"},{\"id\":\"119b3371\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p><strong>What is Depression?<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Depression (major depressive disorder) is a common and severe medical condition that has a negative impact on how you feel, think, and act.<\\/p><p>The mood disorder may appear out of nowhere or after a loss or tragic tragedy, resulting in persistent emotions of despair, worthlessness, hopelessness, helplessness, negativity, or guilt. Depression also makes it difficult to concentrate, stay motivated, and perform other basic tasks.<\\/p><p><strong>Causes of Depression<\\/strong><\\/p><p>The minds of people who have depression look different from those who do not, according to research using brain-imaging technology such as Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI).<\\/p><ul><li>Abuse of any kind, whether physical, sexual, or emotional, can lead to an increased risk of depression later in life.<\\/li><li>Death or a loss<\\/li><li>Personal problems<\\/li><li>Major events<\\/li><li>Genes<\\/li><li>Certain medications<\\/li><li>Age<\\/li><\\/ul><p><strong>Treatment of Depression<\\/strong><\\/p><p>Psychotherapy is often referred to as talk therapy is a technique of assisting persons suffering from a wide range of mental illnesses and emotional problems.<\\/p><p>Interpersonal Therapy, the purpose of this form of treatment is to assist you in improving your relationship skills, such as communication and conflict resolution.<\\/p><p>Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) is a type of talk therapy that aims to help you change any negative thought or behavior patterns that are contributing to or worsening your depression.<\\/p><p>Psychodynamic therapy is a type of therapy where you will understand how your depression may be connected to prior events, unsolved conflicts, or unhealed wounds throughout these treatment sessions.<\\/p><p>Behavioral activation shows you how to develop goals and include more enjoyable activities in your daily routine.<\\/p><p>Family or Couples Therapy. This type of therapy also includes informing your family and friends about depression and how it affects you.<\\/p>\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Roboto Slab\",\"typography_font_weight\":\"400\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
