(1821, 322, '_elementor_data', '[{\"id\":\"57fb893d\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"736d6053\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"9ef21ce\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"image\":{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/localhost\\/aira\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/07\\/pexels-jessica-ticozzelli-4333614.jpg\",\"id\":323}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"image\"},{\"id\":\"4cf9d636\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>\\u201cI understand your pain. Trust me, I do. I\\u2019ve seen people go from the darkest moments in their lives to living a happy, fulfilling life. You can do it too. I believe in you. You are not a burden. You will NEVER BE a burden.\\u201d \\u2014 Sophie Turner<\\/p><p>\\u201cThe experience I have had is that once you start talking about [experiencing a mental health struggle], you realize that actually, you\\u2019re part of quite a big club.\\u201d \\u2014 Prince Harry<\\/p><p>\\u201cI didn\\u2019t want my picture taken because I was going to cry. I didn\\u2019t know why I was going to cry, but I knew that if anybody spoke to me or looked at me too closely the tears would fly out of my eyes and the sobs would fly out of my throat and I\\u2019d cry for a week. I could feel the tears brimming and sloshing in me like water in a glass that is unsteady and too full.\\u201d\\u2015 Sylvia Plath<\\/p><p>Anything that\\u2019s human is mentionable, and anything that is mentionable can be more manageable. When we can talk about our feelings, they become less overwhelming, less upsetting, and less scary.\\u201d \\u2014 Fred Rogers<\\/p><p>\\u201cYou look at me and cry; everything hurts. I hold you and whisper: but everything can heal.\\u201d \\u2015 Rupi Kaur<\\/p><p>\\u201cLife doesn\\u2019t make any sense without interdependence. We need each other, and the sooner we learn that the better for us all.\\u201d\\u00a0 \\u2014 Erik Erikson<\\/p><p>\\u201cMental health problems don\\u2019t define who you are. They are something you experience. You walk in the rain and you feel the rain, but, importantly, YOU ARE NOT THE RAIN.\\u201d \\u2014 Matt Haig<\\/p><p>\\u201cThe advice I\\u2019d give to somebody that\\u2019s silently struggling is, you don\\u2019t have to live that way. You don\\u2019t have to struggle in silence. You can be un-silent. You can live well with a mental health condition, as long as you open up to somebody about it, because it\\u2019s really important you share your experience with people so that you can get the help that you need.\\u201d \\u2014 Demi Lovato<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
