(1842, 327, '_elementor_data', '[{\"id\":\"de0ffff\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"2b7c72bc\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"1cb5c02\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"image\":{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/localhost\\/aira\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/07\\/pexels-cottonbro-3693055.jpg\",\"id\":328}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"image\"},{\"id\":\"4c6bfadb\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>\\u201cIt\\u2019s so difficult to describe depression to someone who\\u2019s never been there, because it\\u2019s not sadness. I know sadness. Sadness is to cry and to feel. But it\\u2019s that cold absence of feeling \\u2014 that really hollowed-out feeling.\\u201d\\u2014 J.K. Rowling<\\/p><p>\\u201cThere are wounds that never show on the body that are deeper and more hurtful than anything that bleeds.\\u201d\\u2015 Laurell K. Hamilton, Mistral\\u2019s Kiss<\\/p><p>\\u201cThat\\u2019s the thing about depression: A human being can survive almost anything, as long as she sees the end in sight. But depression is so insidious, and it compounds daily, that it\\u2019s impossible to ever see the end.\\u2015 Elizabeth Wurtzel, Prozac Nation<\\/p><p>\\u201cPeople who have never dealt with depression think it\\u2019s just being sad or being in a bad mood. That\\u2019s not what depression is for me; it\\u2019s falling into a state of grayness and numbness.\\u201d \\u2014 Dan Reynolds<\\/p><p>\\u201cI go through a lot of depression, and I know other people do, too, but I have an outlet that so many people don\\u2019t. If you have that inside of you and can\\u2019t get it out, what do you do?\\u201d \\u2013 Billie Eilish<\\/p><p>\\u201cA big part of depression is feeling really lonely, even if you\\u2019re in a room full of a million people.\\u201d \\u2014 Lilly Singh<\\/p><p>\\u201cWhen you\\u2019re surrounded by all these people, it can be lonelier than when you\\u2019re by yourself. You can be in a huge crowd, but if you don\\u2019t feel like you can trust anyone or talk to anybody, you feel like you\\u2019re really alone.\\u201d \\u2015 Fiona Apple<\\/p><p>\\u201cI\\u2019ll never forget how the depression and loneliness felt good and bad at the same time. Still does.\\u201d\\u2015 Henry Rollins, The Portable Henry Rollins<\\/p><p>\\u201cI have depression. But I prefer to say, \\u2018I battle\\u2019 depression instead of \\u2018I suffer with it. Because depression hits, but I hit back. Battle on.\\u201d \\u2014 Anonymous<\\/p><p>\\u201cWhen you\\u2019re depressed you don\\u2019t control your thoughts, your thoughts control you. I wish people understood that.\\u201d \\u2014 Anonymous<\\/p><p>\\u201cDepression is feeling like you\\u2019ve lost something but having no clue when or where you last had it. Then one day you realize what you lost is yourself.\\u201d \\u2014 Anonymous<\\/p><p>\\u201cPeople think depression is sadness. People think depression is crying. People think depression is dressing in black. But people are wrong. Depression is the constant feeling of being numb. Being numb to emotions, being numb to life. You wake up in the morning just to go to bed again.\\u201d \\u2014 Anonymous<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
