(1986, 348, '_elementor_data', '[{\"id\":\"70252636\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"56d8a44b\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"54e4228\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"image\":{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/localhost\\/aira\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/07\\/pexels-alex-green-5700171.jpg\",\"id\":349}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"image\"},{\"id\":\"63ec1ab2\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>\\u201cNo need to hurry. No need to sparkle. No need to be anybody but oneself.\\u201d \\u2014Virginia Woolf<\\/p><p>\\u201cWhat does your anxiety do? It does not empty tomorrow of its sorrow, but it empties today of its strength. It does not make you escape the evil; it makes you unfit to cope with it if it comes.\\u201d \\u2015 Raymond L. Cramer<\\/p><p>\\u201cIf you want to conquer the anxiety of life, live in the moment, live in the breath.\\u201d \\u2014 Amit Ray<\\/p><p>\\u201cAnxiety does not empty tomorrow of its sorrows, but only empties today of its strength.\\u201d \\u2014Charles Spurgeon<\\/p><p>\\u201cHow much pain have cost us the evils which have never happened.\\u201d \\u2014Thomas Jefferson<\\/p><p>\\u201cWe must have a pie. Stress cannot exist in the presence of a pie.\\u201d \\u2014David Mamet<\\/p><p>\\u201cAnxiety is a thin stream of fear trickling through the mind. If encouraged, it cuts a channel into which all other thoughts are drained.\\u201d \\u2014Arthur Somers Roche<\\/p><p>\\u201cNothing diminishes anxiety faster than action.\\u201d \\u2014Walter Anderson<\\/p><p>\\u201c[Slow breathing] is like an anchor in the midst of an emotional storm: the anchor won\\u2019t make the storm goes away, but it will hold you steady until it passes. \\u2014 Russ Harris<\\/p><p>\\u201cAnxiety does not empty tomorrow of its sorrows, but only empties today of its strength.\\u201d \\u2014 Charles Spurgeon<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
