(2012, 357, '_elementor_data', '[{\"id\":\"7319f71f\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":[],\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"13c5fe24\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"d727cea\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"image\":{\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/localhost\\/aira\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2021\\/07\\/pexels-andrea-piacquadio-3758110.jpg\",\"id\":354}},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"image\"},{\"id\":\"2801e00b\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>\\u201cSelf-care is never a selfish act\\u2014it is simply good stewardship of the only gift I have, the gift I was put on earth to offer to others.\\u201d \\u2014 Parker Palmer<\\/p><p>\\u201cI found in my research that the biggest reason people aren\'t more self-compassionate is that they are afraid they\\u2019ll become self-indulgent. They believe self-criticism is what keeps them in line. Most people have gotten it wrong because our culture says being hard on yourself is the way to be.\\u201d \\u2014 Kristen Neff<\\/p><p>\\u201cSometimes self-care is exercise and eating right. Sometimes it\\u2019s spending time with loved ones or taking a nap. And sometimes it\\u2019s watching an entire season of TV in one weekend while you lounge around in your pajamas. Whatever soothes your soul.\\u201d \\u2014 Nanea Hoffman<\\/p><p>\\u201cThe best thing you could do is master the chaos in you. You are not thrown into the fire, you are the fire.\\u201d \\u2014 Mama Indigo<\\/p><p>\\u201cUntil you make the unconscious conscious, it will direct your life and you will call it fate.\\u201d \\u2014 Carl Jung<\\/p><p>\\u201cBeauty is how you feel inside, and it reflects in your eyes. It is not something physical.\\u201d \\u2014 Sophia Loren<\\/p><p>\\u201cAccept yourself, love yourself, and keep moving forward. If you want to fly, you have to give up what weighs you down.\\u201d \\u2014 Roy T. Bennett<\\/p><p>\\u201cDeep breathing is our nervous system\\u2019s love language.\\u201d \\u2014 Dr. Lauren Fogel Mersy<\\/p><p>\\u201cDon\\u2019t believe everything you think.\\u201d\\u00a0 \\u2014 Unknown<\\/p><p>\\u201cYou don\\u2019t have to control your thoughts. You just have to stop letting them control you.\\u201d\\u00a0 \\u2014 Dan Millman<\\/p><p>\\u201cThat was the crux. You. Only you could work on you. Nobody could force you, and if you weren\\u2019t ready, then you weren\\u2019t ready, and no amount of open-armed encouragement was going to change that.\\u201d \\u2015 Norah Vincent<\\/p>\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false}]'),
