(168, 1, '2021-07-08 10:00:59', '2021-07-08 10:00:59', 'What is anxiety?\r\nAnxiety disorders are serious mental illnesses that cause persistent anxiety or fear, which can worsen over time. We all experience anxiety from time to time, but with an anxiety disorder, the anxiety is more persistent and has a significant negative impact on a person\'s quality of life.\r\n\r\nTypes of Anxiety Disorders\r\nGeneralized anxiety disorder (GAD) is a specific type of anxiety disorder. Most individuals worry about their health, job, money, and family from time to time, but persons with GAD worry about these things and more in a persistent, excessive, and intense way.\r\nObsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD) is a mental health illness characterized by obsessions and compulsions. Because patients with OCD typically experience extreme anxiety as a result of obsessive thoughts, it was previously characterized as an anxiety disorder. They may also engage in complex routines in an attempt to ease the distress brought on by obsessive thoughts.\r\nPanic Disorder. A person suffering from panic disorder may have symptoms such as intense terror, rapid breathing, and a fast heart rate. These attacks can occur unexpectedly and for no apparent cause in people with panic disorder, but they can also be triggered by a triggering event or scenario.\r\nPost-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) is a mental health illness in which people suffer from a wide range of symptoms after experiencing a traumatic event. Flashbacks, nightmares, intrusive thoughts, anxiety, avoidance, mood, and thinking changes are all possible.\r\nSocial anxiety disorder (SAD) is a mental health condition characterized by a fear of being judged badly in social situations, such as performing or speaking in front of everyone.\r\n\r\nCauses of Anxiety\r\nResearchers are discovering more about these links all the time.\r\nImagining the future\r\nGenetics\r\nEnvironment\r\nIntense stress level\r\nBrain changes\r\nTrauma\r\n\r\nTreatment of Anxiety\r\nAnxiety problems are typically treated successfully with psychotherapy and lifestyle changes, either alone or in combination with medication. One of the most successful treatments is cognitive-behavioral therapy (CBT), which is targeted at an individual\'s specific worries. Patients are taught to question the faulty mental patterns that cause them so much pain.', 'Anxiety', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '161-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-07-08 10:00:59', '2021-07-08 10:00:59', '', 161, 'http://localhost/aira/?p=168', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(169, 1, '2021-07-08 10:35:18', '2021-07-08 10:35:18', '<img width=\"1024\" height=\"683\" src=\"http://localhost/aira/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/pexels-dids-5616284.jpg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" />															\n		<p><strong>What is Depression?</strong></p><p>Depression (major depressive disorder) is a common and severe medical condition that has a negative impact on how you feel, think, and act.</p><p>The mood disorder may appear out of nowhere or after a loss or tragic tragedy, resulting in persistent emotions of despair, worthlessness, hopelessness, helplessness, negativity, or guilt. Depression also makes it difficult to concentrate, stay motivated, and perform other basic tasks.</p><p><strong>Causes of Depression</strong></p><p>The minds of people who have depression look different from those who do not, according to research using brain-imaging technology such as Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI).</p><ul><li>Abuse of any kind, whether physical, sexual, or emotional, can lead to an increased risk of depression later in life.</li><li>Death or a loss</li><li>Personal problems</li><li>Major events</li><li>Genes</li><li>Certain medications</li><li>Age</li></ul><p><strong>Treatment of Depression</strong></p><p>Psychotherapy is often referred to as talk therapy is a technique of assisting persons suffering from a wide range of mental illnesses and emotional problems.</p><p>Interpersonal Therapy, the purpose of this form of treatment is to assist you in improving your relationship skills, such as communication and conflict resolution.</p><p>Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) is a type of talk therapy that aims to help you change any negative thought or behavior patterns that are contributing to or worsening your depression.</p><p>Psychodynamic therapy is a type of therapy where you will understand how your depression may be connected to prior events, unsolved conflicts, or unhealed wounds throughout these treatment sessions.</p><p>Behavioral activation shows you how to develop goals and include more enjoyable activities in your daily routine.</p><p>Family or Couples Therapy. This type of therapy also includes informing your family and friends about depression and how it affects you.</p>', 'Depression', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'depression', '', '', '2021-07-09 03:10:51', '2021-07-09 03:10:51', '', 0, 'http://localhost/aira/?page_id=169', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(170, 1, '2021-07-08 10:35:18', '2021-07-08 10:35:18', 'What is Depression?\r\n\r\nDepression (major depressive disorder) is a common and severe medical condition that has a negative impact on how you feel, think, and act.\r\n\r\nThe mood disorder may appear out of nowhere or after a loss or tragic tragedy, resulting in persistent emotions of despair, worthlessness, hopelessness, helplessness, negativity, or guilt. Depression also makes it difficult to concentrate, stay motivated, and perform other basic tasks.\r\n\r\nCauses of Depression\r\n\r\nThe minds of people who have depression look different from those who do not, according to research using brain-imaging technology such as Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI).\r\n\r\nAbuse in any kind, whether physical, sexual, or emotional, can lead to increased risk to depression later in life.\r\n\r\nDeath or a loss\r\n\r\nPersonal problems\r\n\r\nMajor events\r\n\r\nGenes\r\n\r\nCertain medications\r\n\r\nAge\r\n\r\nTreatment of Depression\r\n\r\nPsychotherapy is often referred to as talk therapy is a technique of assisting persons suffering from a wide range of mental illnesses and emotional problems.\r\n\r\nInterpersonal Therapy, the purpose of this form of treatment is to assist you in improving your relationship skills, such as communication and conflict resolution.\r\n\r\nCognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) is a type of talk therapy that aims to help you change any negative thought or behavior patterns that are contributing to or worsening your depression.\r\n\r\nPsychodynamic therapy is a type of therapy were you will understand how your depression may be connected to prior events, unsolved conflicts, or unhealed wounds throughout these treatment sessions.\r\n\r\nBehavioral activation shows you how to develop goals and include more enjoyable activities into your daily routine.\r\n\r\nFamily or Couples Therapy. This type of therapy also include informing your family and friends about depression and how it affects you.', 'Depression', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '169-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-07-08 10:35:18', '2021-07-08 10:35:18', '', 169, 'http://localhost/aira/?p=170', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
