(172, 1, '2021-07-08 10:45:44', '2021-07-08 10:45:44', '<img width=\"1024\" height=\"536\" src=\"http://localhost/aira/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/anorexia-featured.jpg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" />															\n		<p><strong>What is Anorexia?</strong></p><p>Anorexia is a mental illness characterized by unhealthy, compulsive, or disordered eating habits. Also characterized by abnormally low body weight, an intense fear of gaining weight, and a distorted perception of weight.</p><p><strong>Causes of Anorexia</strong></p><p>Concerns about body weight and shape are often features of anorexia.</p><ul><li>Low self-esteem</li><li>Sexual abuse</li><li>Anxiety</li><li>History of teasing or bullying, especially about weight or body shape</li><li>Pressure from society</li></ul><p><strong>Treatment of Anorexia</strong></p><p>Cognitive-Behavioral Therapy (CBT), which can help the person find new ways of thinking, behaving, and managing stress.</p><p>Nutritional therapy, which provides information on how to use food to build and maintain health.</p><p>Supplements to resolve nutritional deficiencies</p><p>Family and individual counseling</p>', 'Anorexia', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'anorexia', '', '', '2021-07-09 03:00:50', '2021-07-09 03:00:50', '', 0, 'http://localhost/aira/?page_id=172', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(173, 1, '2021-07-08 10:45:44', '2021-07-08 10:45:44', 'What is Anorexia?\r\n\r\nAnorexia is a mental illness characterized by unhealthy, compulsive, or disordered eating habits. Also characterized by abnormally low body weight, an intense fear of gaining weight, and a distorted perception of weight.\r\n\r\nCauses of Anorexia\r\n\r\nConcerns about body weight and shape are often features of anorexia.\r\n\r\nLow self-esteem\r\n\r\nSexual abuse\r\n\r\nAnxiety\r\n\r\nHistory of teasing or bullying, especially about weight or body shape\r\n\r\nPressure from society\r\n\r\nTreatment of Anorexia\r\n\r\nCognitive-Behavioral Therapy (CBT), which can help the person find new ways of thinking, behaving, and managing stress.\r\n\r\nNutritional therapy, which provides information on how to use food to build and maintain health.\r\n\r\nSupplements to resolve nutritional deficiencies\r\n\r\nFamily and individual counseling', 'Anorexia', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '172-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-07-08 10:45:44', '2021-07-08 10:45:44', '', 172, 'http://localhost/aira/?p=173', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
