(259, 1, '2021-07-09 03:08:32', '2021-07-09 03:08:32', 'What is Bipolar Disorder?\r\n\r\nBipolar disorder is a mental illness characterized by periods of severe mood swings that affect emotion, thoughts, and behavior.\r\n\r\nBipolar disorder is divided into two types: Bipolar I and Bipolar II. Bipolar I may or may not be accompanied by a significant depressive episode, while bipolar II does. People with bipolar I have experienced at least one manic episode, which can be severe and require hospitalization. Bipolar II patients typically experience a significant depressive episode that lasts at least two weeks, as well as hypomania, or manic episodes.\r\n\r\nCauses of Bipolar Disorder\r\n\r\nNobody has a clear answer about what really causes bipolar disorder. There is a genetic component to bipolar disorder, according to studies, but DNA isn\'t the only factor. Physical and environmental factors, according to most studies, are likely to be involved.\r\n\r\nEnvironmental Triggers\r\n\r\n( For Depressive Episodes )\r\n\r\nSleep disruption\r\n\r\nPhysical injury or illness\r\n\r\nMenstruation\r\n\r\nLack of exercise\r\n\r\nTravel\r\n\r\n( For Manic Episodes )\r\n\r\nLack of Sleep\r\n\r\nArguments\r\n\r\nBad Breakup or Failed Marriage\r\n\r\nAlcohol Abuse and Drug Intoxication\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nTreatment of Bipolar Disorder\r\n\r\nPsychological Therapies should be performed with skilled mental health specialists who can assist you in recognizing when your moods are changing, identifying triggers that lead to depressive or manic episodes, and developing coping skills for bipolar disorder.\r\n\r\nPrescription Medications. A psychiatrist will determine which medications are most likely to be effective in treating your symptoms. Your medications may need to be adjusted or changed at times.', 'Bipolar Disorder', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '164-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-07-09 03:08:32', '2021-07-09 03:08:32', '', 164, 'http://localhost/aira/?p=259', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
