(261, 1, '2021-07-09 03:08:34', '2021-07-09 03:08:34', '<img width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"http://localhost/aira/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/1v6cbveq4ka11.png\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" />															\n		<p><strong>What is Bipolar Disorder?</strong></p><p>Bipolar disorder is a mental illness characterized by periods of severe mood swings that affect emotion, thoughts, and behavior.</p><p>Bipolar disorder is divided into two types: Bipolar I and Bipolar II. Bipolar I may or may not be accompanied by a significant depressive episode, while bipolar II does. People with bipolar I have experienced at least one manic episode, which can be severe and require hospitalization. Bipolar II patients typically experience a significant depressive episode that lasts at least two weeks, as well as hypomania, or manic episodes.</p><p><strong>Causes of Bipolar Disorder</strong></p><p>Nobody has a clear answer about what really causes bipolar disorder. There is a genetic component to bipolar disorder, according to studies, but DNA isn\'t the only factor. Physical and environmental factors, according to most studies, are likely to be involved.</p><p>Environmental Triggers</p><p>( <em>For Depressive Episodes</em> )</p><ul><li>Sleep disruption</li><li>Physical injury or illness</li><li>Menstruation</li><li>Lack of exercise</li><li>Travel</li></ul><p>( <em>For Manic Episodes</em> )</p><ul><li>Lack of Sleep</li><li>Arguments</li><li>Bad Breakup or Failed Marriage</li><li>Alcohol Abuse and Drug Intoxication</li></ul><p><strong>Treatment of Bipolar Disorder</strong></p><p>Psychological Therapies should be performed with skilled mental health specialists who can assist you in recognizing when your moods are changing, identifying triggers that lead to depressive or manic episodes, and developing coping skills for bipolar disorder.</p><p>Prescription Medications. A psychiatrist will determine which medications are most likely to be effective in treating your symptoms. Your medications may need to be adjusted or changed at times.</p>', 'Bipolar Disorder', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '164-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-07-09 03:08:34', '2021-07-09 03:08:34', '', 164, 'http://localhost/aira/?p=261', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
