(269, 1, '2021-07-09 03:13:26', '2021-07-09 03:13:26', 'What is Schizophrenia?\r\n\r\nSchizophrenia is a mental disorder that disrupts the normal functioning of the brain. This causes persistent issues with disordered thoughts and behaviors, as well as symptoms like hallucinations, delusions, and a lack of emotional expressiveness.\r\n\r\nCauses of Schizophrenia\r\n\r\nScientists are studying many possible factors that might cause a person with a genetic predisposition to develop schizophrenia.\r\n\r\nGenetic factors\r\n\r\nFamily relationships\r\n\r\nAlcohol and other drug use\r\n\r\nStress\r\n\r\nTreatment of Schizophrenia\r\n\r\nPsychotherapy can assist in the normalization of cognitive patterns. People with schizophrenia can also benefit from learning to cope with stress and recognizing early warning signs of illness.\r\n\r\nTraining in social skills. This focuses on increasing communication and social connections, as well as improving daily activities participation.\r\n\r\nTherapy for the whole family. Families suffering from schizophrenia receive assistance and information through this program.\r\n\r\nAntipsychotic pharmaceuticals are the most commonly given antipsychotic medications, which are the cornerstone of schizophrenia treatment. They\'re considered to work by stimulating the dopamine neurotransmitter in the brain.', 'Schizophrenia', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '175-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-07-09 03:13:26', '2021-07-09 03:13:26', '', 175, 'http://localhost/aira/?p=269', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
