(271, 1, '2021-07-09 03:13:28', '2021-07-09 03:13:28', '<img width=\"1024\" height=\"680\" src=\"http://localhost/aira/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/992625.jpg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" />															\n		<p><strong>What is Schizophrenia?</strong></p><p>Schizophrenia is a mental disorder that disrupts the normal functioning of the brain. This causes persistent issues with disordered thoughts and behaviors, as well as symptoms like hallucinations, delusions, and a lack of emotional expressiveness.</p><p><strong>Causes of Schizophrenia</strong></p><p>Scientists are studying many possible factors that might cause a person with a genetic predisposition to develop schizophrenia.</p><ul><li>Genetic factors</li><li>Family relationships</li><li>Alcohol and other drug use</li><li>Stress</li></ul><p><strong>Treatment of Schizophrenia</strong></p><p>Psychotherapy can assist in the normalization of cognitive patterns. People with schizophrenia can also benefit from learning to cope with stress and recognizing early warning signs of illness.</p><p>Training in social skills. This focuses on increasing communication and social connections, as well as improving daily activities participation.</p><p>Therapy for the whole family. Families suffering from schizophrenia receive assistance and information through this program.</p><p>Antipsychotic pharmaceuticals are the most commonly given antipsychotic medications, which are the cornerstone of schizophrenia treatment. They\'re considered to work by stimulating the dopamine neurotransmitter in the brain.</p>', 'Schizophrenia', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '175-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-07-09 03:13:28', '2021-07-09 03:13:28', '', 175, 'http://localhost/aira/?p=271', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
