(305, 1, '2021-07-09 05:31:51', '2021-07-09 05:31:51', 'Modern society has developed some negative associations with the idea of being alone. Being alone does not always mean loneliness, and many people might feel lonely even when they are surrounded by others.\r\n\r\nLearning to spend time alone is important for your mental health and personal development. Perhaps the most important benefit of isolation is that it allows you to understand more about yourself.\r\n\r\n<strong>The Benefits of Being Alone</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>It Makes Your Interests a Priority</em>\r\n\r\nWhen you\'re surrounded by people, it\'s easy to put your own ideas and passions to rest in order to meet the wants and expectations of your friends and family. Taking time to yourself allows you to make creative decisions and focus your attention without being distracted by what others are thinking.\r\n\r\n<em>It improves your mental well-being</em>\r\n\r\nPeople who learn to find comfort in isolation are happier, have lower stress levels, and are less prone to develop depression, according to studies.\r\n\r\n<em>It Boosts Creativity</em>\r\n\r\nPeople who work alone are often better at solving complex problems, according to a study. My alone time is extremely important to me. It allows me to take a step back, think, and most importantly, let my thoughts wander.', 'Why Alone Time Is Important', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'why-alone-time-is-important', '', '', '2021-07-09 05:41:22', '2021-07-09 05:41:22', '', 0, 'http://localhost/aira/?p=305', 0, 'post', '', 0),
